gl_printf() - DERP OS man page

Name -------------------
gl_printf() - puts a string on the scren buffer at the cursor location

Synopsis ---------------

#include "gl_printf.h"

int gl_printf(const char *format, ...);

Description ------------

The gl_printf function draws a string at the current cursor loccation of 
the user screen buffer. It uses gl.h/draw_character ultimately to draw to 
the screen.

	This functoion supports the following formats:
		%d - decimal integer
		%x - hexdecimal
		%X - Unsigned hexadecimal integer (capital letters)
		%u - Unsigned decimal integer
		%s - string

Return Value -----------

No return value, side effects are a string drawn in the screen buffer.
